          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The new graphics state is a copy of the previous state that can be modified to handle new drawing operations.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Saving the graphics state saves such attributes as the current drawing style, transformation matrix, color, and font. To set drawing style attributes, use the methods of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSBezierPath",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Other attributes are accessed through appropriate objects such as ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsaffinetransform",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSColor",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.appkit/documentation/AppKit/NSFont",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
